11 An Act relating to the education initiatives;
defining terms; providing the Education Initiative
12 Revolving Fund shall be used for a competitive grants
pool to fund education initiatives meant to further
13 and improve the education of Oklahoma students;
directing the State Department of Education to
14 administer grant program; authoring the State Board
of Education to award one or more competitive grants
15 to qualifying entities to fund education initiatives;
requiring grants be awarded based on approved rubric;
16 listing required information to be submitted in grant
applications; requiring identifying information be
17 removed before evaluation by Board; requiring use of
rubric for scoring and ranking of grant applications;
18 directing grant application scores be made public
before Board vote; requiring Board to vote to approve
19 grant application and amount to be awarded; creating
the Education Initiative Revolving Fund; providing
20 for codification; and providing an effective date.
21
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
24
Req. No. 17387 Page 1

1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-123.2 of Title 70, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. As used in this section:
5 1. "Board" means the Oklahoma State Board of Education;
6 2. "Department" means the Oklahoma State Department of
7 Education; and
8 3. "Education initiative" means a structured program aimed at
9 improving learning outcomes, solving specific educational
10 challenges, or designed to promote student achievement; and
11 4. "Qualifying entity" means any for-profit or nonprofit
12 corporation, partnership, limited liability company, association, or
13 any other legal or commercial entity.
14 B. The Education Initiative Revolving Fund created pursuant to
15 Section 2 of this act shall be used for a competitive grants pool to
16 fund education initiatives meant to further and improve the
17 education of Oklahoma students. The Department shall administer the
18 competitive grant program. Contingent upon the availability of
19 funds in the Education Initiative Revolving Fund created pursuant to
20 Section 2 of this act, the Board shall award one or more competitive
21 grants to qualifying entities to fund education initiatives to be
22 implemented within this state.
23 C. 1. Grants shall be awarded to qualifying entities based on
24 a rubric designed by the Department and approved by the Board.
Req. No. 17387 Page 2

1 2. Grant applications shall include, but are not limited to:
2 a. a description of the education initiative,
3 b. what educational need the education initiative will
4 serve,
5 c. the dollar amount requested,
6 d. the population to be served,
7 e. what metrics will be used to evaluate the efficacy of
8 the education initiative, and
9 f. if the education initiative has already been
10 implemented in any school districts within this state,
11 the data from that education initiative and the
12 efficacy of the education initiative.
13 3. Before any grant application is evaluated by the Board, all
14 identifying information shall be removed from the grant application.
15 The Board shall score grant applications using the approved rubric
16 and rank the applications according to the evaluation score. Final
17 scores of the grant application shall be made public prior to any
18 vote by the Board. The Board shall vote to approve a grant
19 application and the amount to be awarded.
20 D. The Board shall promulgate rules as necessary to administer
21 the competitive grant program created in this section.
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-123.3 of Title 70, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 17387 Page 3

1 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
2 for the State Department of Education to be designated the
3 "Education Initiative Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a
4 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
5 consist of all monies received by the State Department of Education
6 from appropriations, gifts, grants, donations, and bequests. All
7 monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated
8 and may be budgeted and expended by the State Department of
9 Education for the purpose of implementing the provisions of Section
10 1 of this act. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon
11 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
12 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
13 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
14 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
